cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the evaluation of machine learning algorithms for biomedical applications, specifically for a seizure detection task based on EEG data. The paper proposes new metrics for evaluating performance and discusses the deficiencies of existing metrics. This work involves deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE), as well as computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) in the context of user acceptance.
